a, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Beatrix","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Late Latin personal name, which was borne by a saint martyred in Rome, together with Saints Faustinus and Simplicius, in the early 4th century. The original form of the name was probably <i>Viatrix</i>, a feminine version of <i>Viator</i> ‘voyager (through life)’, which was a favourite name among early Christians. This was then altered by association with Latin <i>Beatus</i> ‘blessed’ (<i>Via-</i> and <i>Bea-</i> sometimes being pronounced the same in Late Latin).  See also  Beatrice ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Beatrix de Foucarmont was born in 0995, in Foucarmont, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France, her father, Clotaire II de Foucarmont, was 47 and her mother, Lucienne de Saint Saëns, was 33. She had at least 1 son with Hugues de Gournay. She died in 1015, in Gournay-en-Bray, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France, at the age of 20."},"et":{"995–1015":"0995–1015","0979–1039":"0979–1039","0982–1034":"0982–1034","0988–1039":"0988–1039","0995–1015":"0995–1015","0990–1074":"0990–1074","1030–1101":"1030–1101","0948–1013":"0948–1013","0962–Female":"0962–Surnud","1074":"1074","1030":"1030","1039":"1039","0962":"0962","0995":"0995","1015":"1015","995":"0995","0982":"0982","1013":"1013","1101":"1101","0990":"0990","1034":"1034","0948":"0948","0979":"0979","0988":"0988","Gournay-en-Bray, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France":"Gournay-en-Bray, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Foucarmont, Seine-Maritime, Upper Normandy, France":"Foucarmont, Seine-Maritime, Haute-Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Sènarpont, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Senarpont, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"995–1015":"0995–1015","0979–1039":"0979–1039","0982–1034":"0982–1034","0988–1039":"0988–1039",